<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[136,1452,1743,1948]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">
This group was proposed for two Asian species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lobl, 1973" authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="1973" box="[710,977,1778,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrops">
<emphasis box="[710,839,1779,1804]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">B. macrops</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lobl I." box="[851,977,1778,1805]" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="157 - 174" part="46" refId="ref15513" refString="Lobl I. 1973. Neue orientalische Arten der Gattung Eubaeocera Cornell (Coleoptera, Scaphidiidae). Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen entomologischen Gesellschaft 46: 157 - 174." title="Neue orientalische Arten der Gattung Eubaeocera Cornell (Coleoptera, Scaphidiidae)" type="journal article" year="1973">Löbl, 1973</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lobl, 1979" authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="1979" box="[1039,1272,1778,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamil">
<emphasis box="[1039,1132,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">B. tamil</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lobl I." box="[1142,1272,1778,1805]" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse de Zoologie" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="77 - 129" part="86" refId="ref15542" refString="Lobl I. 1979. Die Scaphidiidae (Coleoptera) Sudindiens. Revue suisse de Zoologie 86: 77 - 129. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 82281" title="Die Scaphidiidae (Coleoptera) Sudindiens" type="journal article" year="1979">Löbl, 1979</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and comprises only three Asian species. They share asymmetrical aedeagi with a large basal bulb and complex internal sac with the members of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lobl" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[324,474,1851,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrosa">
<emphasis box="[324,474,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">B. monstrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Lobl I." box="[612,734,1850,1877]" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse de Zoologie" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="77 - 129" part="86" refId="ref15542" refString="Lobl I. 1979. Die Scaphidiidae (Coleoptera) Sudindiens. Revue suisse de Zoologie 86: 77 - 129. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 82281" title="Die Scaphidiidae (Coleoptera) Sudindiens" type="journal article" year="1979">Löbl 1979</bibRefCitation>
). The members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="1973" box="[996,1124,1851,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrops">
<emphasis box="[996,1124,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">B. macrops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group may be distinguished by narrow parameres, narrow bifurcate apex of the median lobe, and the internal sacs bearing rows of denticles and lacking large sclerotized pieces.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
